Sentencas: The electrochemical oxidation of catalytic grown carbon fiber has been examined in a direct carbon fuel cell (DCFC).
Titulo: Electrochemical oxidation of catalytic grown carbon fiber in a direct carbon fuel cell using Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-carbonate electrolyte

Sentencas: The single cell contains a composite electrolyte layer made of a samarium doped ceria (SDC) and a eutectic carbonate phase.
Titulo: Electrochemical oxidation of catalytic grown carbon fiber in a direct carbon fuel cell using Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-carbonate electrolyte

Sentencas: The cathode is a mixture of lithiated NiO and the composite electrolyte, while the anode is composed of NiO and SDC powder.
Titulo: Electrochemical oxidation of catalytic grown carbon fiber in a direct carbon fuel cell using Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-carbonate electrolyte

Sentencas: Catalytic carbon fiber and the eutectic carbonate is premixed and used as the feed of the anode fuel.
Titulo: Electrochemical oxidation of catalytic grown carbon fiber in a direct carbon fuel cell using Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-carbonate electrolyte

Sentencas: The effects of the cell pellet configuration, cathode gas composition and the operation temperature on the DCFC performance have been examined in this work.
Titulo: Electrochemical oxidation of catalytic grown carbon fiber in a direct carbon fuel cell using Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-carbonate electrolyte

Sentencas: At 700 degrees C, the maximum power output achieves 112 mW cm(-2) with a current density of 249 mA cm(-2).
Titulo: Electrochemical oxidation of catalytic grown carbon fiber in a direct carbon fuel cell using Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-carbonate electrolyte

Sentencas: The anode off-gas is analyzed with a gas chromatograph, and the Boudouard reaction is found suppressed by the electrical field in the fuel cell operation.
Titulo: Electrochemical oxidation of catalytic grown carbon fiber in a direct carbon fuel cell using Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-carbonate electrolyte
